441
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:18,880
How old are you?

442
00:26:19,590 --> 00:26:21,790
I'm 25.

443
00:26:21,910 --> 00:26:22,910
Oh.

444
00:26:23,150 --> 00:26:24,390
But I'm only 24.

445
00:26:24,670 --> 00:26:26,350
I should call you "Ma'am."

446
00:26:26,830 --> 00:26:27,830
Ma'am.

447
00:26:34,710 --> 00:26:35,990
A sound is coming from that place.

448
00:26:35,990 --> 00:26:37,120
Let's go take a look.

449
00:26:39,230 --> 00:26:41,630
I'm scared. I'll be waiting here for you.

450
00:26:41,790 --> 00:26:42,790
Okay.

451
00:27:24,990 --> 00:27:28,390
Ancient remedies and miracle drugs help restore health.

452
00:27:28,990 --> 00:27:33,270
Effective cures eliminate the falsehood from the truth.

453
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:36,270
Gentlemen, care to give it a try?

454
00:27:38,150 --> 00:27:39,310
No, madam.

455
00:27:39,790 --> 00:27:41,110
I'd like to ask you something.

456
00:27:41,110 --> 00:27:42,670
What kind of story does the mural

457
00:27:42,670 --> 00:27:44,600
in the exhibition hall try to tell?

458
00:27:45,750 --> 00:27:48,790
Two sisters attend a funeral,

459
00:27:49,350 --> 00:27:53,070
during which the younger one falls in love with a young man.

460
00:27:53,830 --> 00:27:56,350
The older one goes home and dies.

461
00:27:57,310 --> 00:28:01,350
What kind of story would you say it is?

462
00:28:03,790 --> 00:28:06,790
It warns people not to easily fall in love with others.

463
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:08,670
Maybe don't bother using your brain.

464
00:28:08,670 --> 00:28:09,670
Just let it rest.

465
00:28:13,350 --> 00:28:16,790
Sir, why don't you try this medicine?

466
00:28:17,470 --> 00:28:18,950
Those in poor health

467
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:21,030
